.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-mesh-models - List models served across reachable mesh nodes


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel mesh models [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Enumerates online peers, probes each node's /status over the mesh, and lists
every served model as a model -> node/engine/port row.

.PP
Only OTHER nodes are shown (this node is excluded). Nodes that do not serve the
status endpoint on the mesh (e.g. plain \fBcitadel work\fR without --gateway) are
skipped.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for models

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	Output in JSON format (includes unreachable nodes)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output

.PP
\fB--port\fP=8080
	Peer status endpoint port to probe over the mesh


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # List all models served across the mesh
  citadel mesh models

  # JSON output (includes unreachable nodes and their errors)
  citadel mesh models --json

  # Probe a non-default status port
  citadel mesh models --port 8080
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel-mesh(1)\fP
